author: Simon Rice For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Sutton v Arsenal: Tickets see huge queues ahead of FA Cup Fifth Round tie | Metro News
text:
Simon Rice for Metro.co.uk Sunday 12 Feb 2017 4:42 pm Sutton after beating Leeds United in the last round (Getty) 
Sutton United taking on Arsenal in the FA Cup is quite a big deal and the queues for tickets prove just how much. 
The non-league side had never reached the Fifth Round of the tournament before and having made it there against all the odds this season they were rewarded with a tie against the 12-time winners. Mesut Ozil suffering CRISIS of confidence, admits Arsenal boss Wenger 
Tickets for the tie at Gander Green Lane went on sale to Sutton United season ticket holders earlier today and it would appear every single one of their die-hard fans turned up to claim them with queues forming from 5am in the morning. 
Pictures posted on Twitter showed the line going around the edge of the pitch at their 5,000 capacity home. The queue for tickets at Sutton United for next week's #Arsenal match. pic.twitter.com/rrruthD4Qd
